  "authoring_notes": {
    "summary": "Adult with severe hypertension, headache, confusion, blurred vision, and evolving encephalopathy. Goal is recognition of hypertensive emergency, controlled BP reduction, appropriate monitoring, and avoidance of precipitous overcorrection.",
    "teaching_focus": [
      "Recognize hypertensive emergency rather than asymptomatic hypertension",
      "Choose a titratable IV antihypertensive",
      "Lower MAP gradually rather than normalizing immediately",
      "Monitor for neurologic worsening from disease progression or overshoot hypoperfusion",
      "Consider PRES / hypertensive encephalopathy and obtain appropriate workup"
    ]
  },
